    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;The Grant Negotiation and Authorization Protocol (GNAP) defines a mechanism for delegating authorization to a piece of software and conveying the results and artifacts of that delegation to the software.  This delegation can include access to a set of APIs as well as subject information passed directly to the software.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
